FBIS4-37755 "drnes122_k_94003" FBIS-NES-94-122 Daily Report 19 Jun 1994 IRAQ APFC Official Meets Yemeni Delegation APFC Official Meets Yemeni Delegation JN1906145794 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1340 GMT 19 Jun 94 JN1906145794 Baghdad INA Arabic BFN [Excerpt] Baghdad, 19 Jun (INA)--Sa'd Qasim Hammudi, secretary general of the Arab Popular Forces Conference [APFC], today received the visiting Yemeni House of Representatives' delegation led by Muhammad 'Abdallah al-Kibsi. In a speech he delivered, Sa'd Qasim Hammudi reiterated that all nationalist and pan-Arab forces in the Arab homeland support Yemen's unity and it constitutional legitimacy against secessionist colonialist attempts, which are backed by reactionaries and are aimed at disrupting Yemen's unity, which is a pan-Arab accomplishment that has been made through huge sacrifices. He added that Yemen's unity constitutes a strength for the Arab nation in its confrontation of the evil, hostile, and reactionary forces threatening the nation's present and future. [passage omitted]
